race.comment: MR HANKY PANKY (3) has hit the top-four in four of his past five starts and looks to be on the doorstep of a maiden victory. Gets the services of Tilley on from a favourable draw and should be going very close. ENIGMA'S CHOICE (7) has been right there in all three career efforts to date and this is not an overly strong affair. Nicely placed to break through. DOTTI BISKIT (4) just ran into one better here before being tipped out for further time to furnish. Tuned up for this with two solid trials and a strong showing while fresh would not surprise. Former Victorian SHE'S BRUTAL (9) is having her first run for the new stable but should find this easier than what she faced down south. Respect any market confidence.
